direction: down

title: |md
  # Arc Flash Hazard Analysis Process
  IEEE 1584-2018 Workflow
| {near: top-center}

phase1: PHASE 1: Data Collection {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8f5e9"
  style.font-size: 18
}

step1: Step 1: Collect System &\nInstallation Data {
  shape: rectangle
}
step1.items: |md
  - Single-line diagrams
  - Equipment ratings
  - Conductor data
  - Protective device settings
  - Instrument transformer data
|

step2: Step 2: Determine System\nModes of Operation {
  shape: rectangle
}
step2.items: |md
  - Maximum fault current
  - Minimum fault current
  - Generator configurations
  - Tie breaker positions
|

step3: Step 3: Calculate Bolted\nFault Currents {
  shape: rectangle
}
step3.items: |md
  - Short-circuit study
  - Multiple source effects
  - Motor contributions
  - Dynamic simulations
|

phase2: PHASE 2: Equipment Analysis {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fff3e0"
  style.font-size: 18
}

step4: Step 4: Determine Gap &\nEnclosure Size {
  shape: rectangle
}
step4.items: |md
  - Use Table 8 for typical gaps
  - Measure actual enclosures
  - Classify enclosure type
  - Determine opening area
|

step5: Step 5: Determine Electrode\nConfiguration {
  shape: rectangle
}
step5.items: |md
  - VCB: Vertical in box
  - VCBB: Vertical with barrier
  - HCB: Horizontal in box
  - VOA: Vertical open air
  - HOA: Horizontal open air
|

step6: Step 6: Determine Working\nDistances {
  shape: rectangle
}
step6.items: |md
  - Use Table 10 for typical
  - Task-specific distances
  - Minimum 305mm (12 in)
|

phase3: PHASE 3: Calculations {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e3f2fd"
  style.font-size: 18
}

step7: Step 7: Calculate\nArcing Current {
  shape: rectangle
}
step7.items: |md
  - Apply Equation 1
  - Consider voltage level
  - Apply variation factor
|

step8: Step 8: Determine\nArc Duration {
  shape: rectangle
}
step8.items: |md
  - Use TCC curves
  - Fuse clearing time
  - CB + relay time
  - 2 second maximum
|

step9: Step 9: Calculate\nIncident Energy {
  shape: rectangle
}
step9.items: |md
  - Apply Equations 3-6
  - Include CF correction
  - Calculate for both Iarc values
  - Consider motor contributions
|

step10: Step 10: Determine\nArc-Flash Boundary {
  shape: rectangle
}
step10.items: |md
  - Apply Equations 7-10
  - 5.0 J/cm² threshold
  - Use maximum value
|

phase4: PHASE 4: Documentation {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f3e5f5"
  style.font-size: 18
}

document: Document Results {
  shape: rectangle
}
document.items: |md
  - Equipment labels
  - Incident energy levels
  - Arc-flash boundaries
  - PPE requirements
  - Study assumptions
|

validate: Validate & Review {
  shape: rectangle
}
validate.items: |md
  - Check model ranges
  - Verify protective devices
  - Review assumptions
  - Quality control
|

complete: Analysis Complete {
  shape: oval
  style.fill: "#c8e6c9"
}

# Connections
phase1 -> step1
step1 -> step2
step2 -> step3

step3 -> phase2
phase2 -> step4
step4 -> step5
step5 -> step6

step6 -> phase3
phase3 -> step7
step7 -> step8
step8 -> step9
step9 -> step10

step10 -> phase4
phase4 -> document
document -> validate
validate -> complete

# Side notes
notes: Critical Considerations {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#ffebee"
  near: top-right
}
notes.1: "⚠ Model valid 208V-15kV"
notes.2: "⚠ Three-phase AC only"
notes.3: "⚠ Multiple calculations needed"
notes.4: "⚠ Select maximum results"
